&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your interest in Oklo!&amp;nbsp; We are searching for a&lt;strong data-renderer-mark=&quot;true&quot;&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Network Systems Technician&lt;strong data-renderer-mark=&quot;true&quot;&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;230&quot; data-local-id=&quot;71fdec52cdb1&quot;&gt;Oklo, Inc. is seeking a skilled and hands-on Network Systems Technician to support and maintain the company’s network infrastructure, endpoint connectivity, and on-site IT systems. This role is focused on ensuring reliable, secure, and high-performing network and systems operations across Oklo’s offices, labs, and collaboration spaces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;569&quot; data-local-id=&quot;7b1196fbb86c&quot;&gt;The Network Systems Technician will work closely with the IT/Cyber team to support daily operations, troubleshoot network and system issues, and assist with infrastructure upgrades in a fast-paced, mission-driven environment. This position is ideal for someone who enjoys being close to the hardware, solving real-world connectivity problems, and providing excellent technical support to users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;569&quot; data-local-id=&quot;7b1196fbb86c&quot;&gt;This is an on-site position in Santa Clara, CA.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
